nodes.title: Notes
widgets_values: I find when I download new LoRAs or find a good prompt, I want to quickly throw it somewhere while I work. You can use these notes to easily do that!

nodes.title: DELETE ME!
widgets_values:
Personally, I use ComfyUI a lot for work, and having tried a number of different nodes and workflows, this has become my go-to workflow. 

I've hidden nodes that I find I never touch, and the settings I use. This workflow focuses on speed (Turbo LoRA https://huggingface.co/alimama-creative/FLUX.1-Turbo-Alpha), adaptability, and quick upscales that let me keep on working.

If you're after the best quality, with the best resolution etc. this workflow may not be for you. This is also may need adjusting if you have VRAM limitations. I use Paperspace and typically the A6000 (48gb VRAM...), but you can definitely adjust accordingly.

nodes.title: DELETE ME!
widgets_values: I sometimes have ~10-15 LoRAs listed, so there's lots of room to quickly switch between them as you work.

nodes.title: DELETE ME!
widgets_values: This uses the Lying Sigma Sampler from https://github.com/Jonseed/ComfyUI-Detail-Daemon. Don't ask me how it works, I just know I get far better detail on initial generations than I did with the regular KSampler. For me, it's my go-to now.
